Call Deadline: 31-Dec-2008 

The Canadian Journal of Linguistics is soliciting proposals for articles
(in either French or English) to go into a special issue on the morphology
of Creole languages. The target date for the special issue is March 2011.
Articles of a theoretical or descriptive nature are welcome, though a
sub-theme for the volume may emerge, depending on the number and nature of
the proposals received. There is a 50 (double-spaced) page limit on
articles. The CJL will adhere to a strict publication deadline, so we must
adhere to the target dates set out below.

The proposals will be submitted to a blind, in-house referee process and
the finished articles will be sent to external reviewers. 

Important dates:

- deadline for the submission of a proposal: December 31st, 2008
- notification of acceptance or rejection of the proposal: January 31st, 2009
- deadline for submission of the article: September 30th, 2009
- articles to be sent out for review: November 15th, 2009
- deadline for submission of the final version of the article: May 31st, 2010
- publication of the volume: March 2011 

Details of the proposal

- No more than one page, plus an additional page for references
- Two copies, one with your name(s) and institutional affiliation(s) and
one without (to be reviewed)
- The proposal should clearly indicate the
- main point of the article
- intended contribution to creolistics (or linguistics more generally) 
- Creole language(s) upon which the article bears

Proposals based on research that is in its initial stages are welcome, as
are those based on ongoing research. 

Proposals may be submitted by email attachment to the following address:

Darlene.lacharite@lli.ulaval.ca

They may be faxed to: 418-656-2622 (attention Darlene LaCharité) or mailed
to the following address: 

Darlene LaCharité,
Département de langues, ling. et traduction
Pav. Charles-De Koninck, 1030 avenue des Sciences-Humaines
Université laval
Québec, Québec (Canada) G1V 0A6






